			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've been soloing in the basilisk caves since I dinged 38 (am now 41). This place is fantastic for soloing, particularily since this area is vastly uninhibited on my server. I also was able to do some exploring in the forest and do some fighting there. <br><br>One thing I really wanted to do with this toon (Siluuilia Caillech is my mage) is to go places, see more and do more then I did with my cleric. My cleric went from the &quot;traditional&quot; places such as OT, DL, Sol, Guk, kedge, ME etc to  Fear, Kael, Vox etc etc. I didn't want to do that with my mage so I am very appreciative of the information people place here on these boards. It's very very refreshing to be able to go somewhere new and be able to stretch my wings =) To be honest I can't stand OT and DL now, so i try to avoid those places like the plague =) Definately try this area, there is even a bank/vendors inside the caves near the oracle. I have over 200 basilisk eggs too <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="razz" border="0" /><br><br>There are caves full of these critters who (with the exception of genitors) do not aggro. I used either fire or water (occasionally air),with a jade bracelet, dagger of symbols, burn out and expedience. I usually pulled by a) using a throwing knife (gotta get that throwing skill up! Tail pulling doesn't seem to get any higher though <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="razz" border="0" />) b) malaise or c) whacking them with cinderbolt if they were a distance away.  I'd send me trusty companion in and heal at 60, occasionally using rain or straight nuke. Perhaps not the best way to solo, but it works for me heehee =) One thing I did notice, however, was that my fire pet turned the basilisks into crispy critters rather quickly - they often would not get below 54% health with no heal and me pulling with a throwing knife or malaise.  Without c3 I was able to successfully pull with very little down time - often going at 30-40% mana each time. Perhaps not the most efficient - but i got used to going on low mana with my cleric heehee <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="razz" border="0" /> <br><br>Also, when i found myself getting a wee bit bored i would venture into the forest and bonk griffons (definately need a fire pet if you can for those ones, they hit very very fast) or bears/wolves. It is definately a good place to go! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=silinye>silinye</A> at: 12/18/02 4:31:57 pm<br></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
