			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There are 16 static basilisk spawns in the caves, 4 in each little cove coming off the main cavern there in Jaggedpine.  All basilisks are on a 6 minute timer.   As has been stated, the genitors will agro if you get close enough, and the regular "a cave basilisks" will neither agro nor will they assist their brothers.  Loot is chunks of meat, basilisk eye stalks, and eggs (eggs only off the genitors).  Great loot if you're working on your baking skill or poison making - poor loot if you're not.
<br />

<br />
Experience slows at 41 a lot, but there are enough spawns that spawn fast enough, that if you can conserve your mana it's still a pretty good exp camp.  It's non-stop fighting.  By the time you finish a few spawns, you have a re-pop of ones you've already killed.  Without c3, I've been able to do about 6 spawns at a time.  Usually I'd have to med after about 24 spawns or so.  
<br />

<br />
Level 41 mage - focused 39 fire pet (worked really well with 34 pet too, you just gotta heal more, so you can take less spawns before the re-pop) - plate armor, focus bracer and ring on pet, 3 dagger of symbols (one should go in the pet's range slot, no?).  Usually, I'll pull with malaise, heal pet at 70%, and hit with DD spell when the mob starts running.  Let sparky sit for 30 seconds or so at the end of the fight and go tag the next one.<br />_________________<br />Lytmaaj Petslinger - just a short little Brell-worshiping gnomie mage on Povar.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
